result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Repeater, Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device] and Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Repeater, Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Repeater, Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (7th, 8th or 9th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Repeater, Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device] was dismissed by the court.

  • Dennis Edward Strabley was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Repeater, Alcohol Fine Enhancer, Penalties for Felonies-Class "H" Felony, Requirement for Ignition Interlock Device], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Dennis Edward Strabley was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Repeater, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
